17 agency upon the order of a licensed physician or a physician assistant acting pursuant to
18 the authority of Code Section 43-34-103. The State Board of Pharmacy shall be
19 authorized to adopt regulations governing the storage, quantity, use, and administration
20 of such items; provided, however, that nothing in this paragraph or in such regulations
21 shall be construed to restrict any authority of nurses existing under other provisions of
22 law;"
23 SECTION 2.
24 Title 31 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to health, is amended by revising
25 paragraph (20) of Code Section 31-6-2, relating to definitions relative to state health planning
26 and development, as follows:
27 "(20) 'Home health agency' means a public agency or private organization, or a
28 subdivision of such an agency or organization, which is primarily engaged in providing
29 to individuals who are under a written plan of care of a physician treatment ordered by
30 a physician or a physician assistant acting pursuant to the authority of Code
31 Section 43-34-103, on a visiting basis in the places of residence used as such individuals'
32 homes, part-time or intermittent nursing care provided by or under the supervision of a
33 registered professional nurse, and one or more of the following services:
34 (A) Physical therapy;
35 (B) Occupational therapy;
36 (C) Speech therapy;
37 (D) Respiratory therapy;
38 (E) Skilled nursing care;
39 (D)(F) Medical social services under the direction of a physician or a physician
40 assistant acting pursuant to the authority of Code Section 43-34-103; or
41 (E)(G) Part-time or intermittent services of a home health aide."
