42 SECTION 3.
43 Said title is further amended by revising Code Section 31-7-150, relating to definitions, as
44 follows:
45 "31-7-150.
46 As used in this article, the term:
47 (1) 'Branch office' means a location or site, identified in the application or endorsement
48 thereto, from which a home health agency provides services within a portion of the total
49 geographic area served by the parent agency and which is part of the home health agency
50 and is located sufficiently close to share administration, supervision, and services in a
51 manner that renders it unnecessary for the branch independently to meet the requirements
52 of this article.
53 (1.1)(2) 'Department' means the Department of Community Health.
54 (2)(3) 'Home health agency' means a public, nonprofit, or proprietary organization,
55 whether owned or operated by one or more persons or legal entities, which is engaged in
56 furnishing home health healthcare services.
57 (3)(4) 'Home health healthcare services' means those items and services furnished to an
58 individual according to a written plan of treatment signed by the patient's physician, or
59 a physician assistant acting pursuant to the authority of Code Section 43-34-103; by a
60 home health agency,; or by others under arrangement with the home health agency, on
61 a visit or hourly basis, in a place of temporary or permanent residence used as the
62 individual's home, as follows:
63 (A) Part-time or intermittent skilled nursing care as ordered by a physician or a
64 physician assistant acting pursuant to the authority of Code Section 43-34-103 and
65 provided by or under the supervision of a registered nurse and at least one other service
66 listed in subparagraphs (B) through (D) of this paragraph;
67 (B) Physical, occupational, or speech therapy;
68 (C) Medical social services; and
- 3 -

