120 federal program for reimbursement of medicare Medicare or Medicaid services."
121 SECTION 6.
122 Title 43 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to professions and businesses,
123 is amended by revising paragraph (1) of subsection (b) of Code Section 43-34-23, relating
124 to the delegation of authority to nurse or physician assistant, and by adding a new paragraph
125 to read as follows:
126 "(b)(1)(A) A physician may delegate the authority contained in subparagraph (B) of
127 this paragraph to:
128 (i) A physician assistant in accordance with a job description; or
129 (ii) A nurse recognized by the Georgia Board of Nursing as a certified nurse midwife,
130 certified registered nurse anesthetist, certified nurse practitioner, or clinical nurse
131 specialist in psychiatric/mental health in accordance with a nurse protocol.
132 (B) A physician may delegate to those healthcare professionals identified in
133 subparagraph (A) of this paragraph:
134 (i) The authority to order controlled substances selected from a formulary of such
135 drugs established by the board and the authority to order dangerous drugs, medical
136 treatments, and diagnostic studies;
137 (ii) The authority to request, receive, and sign for professional samples and to
138 distribute professional samples to patients. The office or facility at which the
139 healthcare professional identified in subparagraph (A) of this paragraph is working
140 shall maintain a general list of the professional samples approved by the delegating
141 physician for request, receipt, and distribution by the healthcare professional
142 identified in subparagraph (A) of this paragraph as well as a complete list of the
143 specific number and dosage of each professional sample and medication voucher
144 received. Professional samples that are distributed by a healthcare professional
