163 SECTION 7.
164 Said title is further amended in Code Section 43-34-103, relating to application for licensure
165 as a physician assistant, authorized delegated authority, and prohibited acts, by adding a new
166 subsection to read as follows:
167 "(m) In addition to and without limiting the authority granted by Code Section 43-34-23,
168 a physician may delegate to a physician assistant, in accordance with a job description, the
169 authority to order home healthcare services to a patient."
