171 Title 48 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to revenue and taxation, is
172 amended by revising paragraph (1) of subsection (a) of Code Section 48-7-29.2, relating to
173 tax credits for qualified caregiving expenses, as follows:
174 "(1) 'Qualified caregiving expenses' means payments by the taxpayer for home health
175 agency services, personal care services, personal care attendant services, homemaker
176 services, adult day care, respite care, or healthcare equipment and supplies which
177 equipment and supplies have been determined to be medically necessary by a physician
178 or a physician assistant acting pursuant to the authority of Code Section 43-34-103, which
179 services, care, or equipment and supplies are:
180 (A) Provided to the qualifying family member; and
181 (B) Purchased or obtained from an organization or individual not related to the
182 taxpayer or the qualifying family member."
